page.title: 04Transport
page.content: Transport in our block consists of {cars,motor bikes,mopeds,bicycles and {buses.}We found out that 67.6% of Tayports people travel about by car.And that{4.1%}travel about by motor bike{1.7%}of the people in Tayport travel about by mopeds and that most of the children have bicycles. There are two long distance lorry drivers,who own their{lorries. We used to have transport by rail and ferry across the river before the Tay road bridge was built in{1966. The{bus service}runs every half hour during weekdays and Saturdays to and from Dundee and ST Andrews.On Sundays they come every one to two hours.
